  187: init_per_testcase(Func, Config) ->
  188:     CaseDir = filename:join(proplists:get_value(priv_dir, Config), Func),
  189:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([CaseDir, dummy_file])),
  190:     true = code:add_patha(CaseDir),
  191:     [{case_dir, CaseDir}|Config].
  192: 
  193: end_per_testcase(_Func, Config) ->
  194:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  195:     unload_modules(CaseDir),
  196:     asn1_test_lib:rm_dirs([CaseDir]),
  197:     code:del_path(CaseDir).
  198: 
  199: unload_modules(CaseDir) ->
  200:     F = fun(Name0, Acc) ->
  201:                 Name1 = filename:rootname(filename:basename(Name0)),
  202:                 Name = list_to_existing_atom(Name1),
  203:                 [Name|Acc]
  204:         end,
  205:     Beams1 = lists:usort(filelib:fold_files(CaseDir, "[.]beam\$", true, F, [])),
  206:     Beams = [M || M <- Beams1, code:is_loaded(M) =/= false],
  207:     _ = [begin
  208:              code:purge(M),
  209:              code:delete(M),
  210:              code:purge(M),
  211:              io:format("Unloaded ~p", [M])
  212:          end || M <- Beams],
  213:     ok.

  215: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  216: %% Test runners
  217: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  218: 
  219: test(Config, TestF) ->
  220:     test(Config, TestF, [per, uper, ber, jer, {ber,[ber,jer]}]).
  221: 
  222: test(Config, TestF, Rules) ->
  223:     Fun = fun(C, R, O) ->
  224:                   M = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, module)),
  225:                   F = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, name)),
  226:                   io:format("Running ~p:~p with ~p...~n", [M, F, {R, O}]),
  227:                   try
  228:                       TestF(C, R, O)
  229:                   catch
  230:                       Class:Reason:Stk ->
  231:                           NewReason = {Reason, [{rule, R}, {options, O}]},
  232:                           erlang:raise(Class, NewReason, Stk)
  233:                   end
  234:           end,
  235:     Result = [run_case(Config, Fun, rule(Rule), opts(Rule)) || Rule <- Rules],
  236:     case lists:usort(Result) of
  237:         [true|_Skips] -> true; % At least one test ran
  238:         Skips        -> {skip, [R || {skip, R} <- Skips]} % All skipped
  239:     end.
  240: 
  241: rule(A) when is_atom(A) -> A;
  242: rule({A, _Opts} )       -> A.
  243: 
  244: opts(Rule) when is_atom(Rule) -> [];
  245: opts({_Rule, Opts})         -> Opts.
  246: 
  247: run_case(Config, Fun, Rule, Opts) ->
  248:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  249:     Dir = filename:join([CaseDir, join(Rule, Opts)]),
  250:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([Dir, dummy_file])),
  251:     replace_path(CaseDir, Dir),
  252:     NewConfig = lists:keyreplace(case_dir, 1, Config, {case_dir, Dir}),
  253: 
  254:     % Run the actual test function
  255:     Result = Fun(NewConfig, Rule, Opts),
  256: 
  257:     replace_path(Dir, CaseDir),
  258:     case Result of
  259:         {skip, _Reason} -> Result;
  260:         _               -> true
  261:     end.
  262: 
  263: replace_path(PathA, PathB) ->
  264:     true = code:del_path(PathA),
  265:     true = code:add_patha(PathB).
  266: 
  267: join(Rule, Opts) ->
  268:     lists:join("_", [atom_to_list(Rule)|lists:map(fun atom_to_list/1, Opts)]).

  274: %% Cover run-time functions that are only called by the ASN.1 compiler
  275: %% (if any).
  276: cover(_) ->
  277:     Wc = filename:join([code:lib_dir(asn1),"ebin","asn1ct_eval_*.beam"]),
  278:     Beams = filelib:wildcard(Wc),
  279:     true = Beams =/= [],
  280:     [begin
  281: 	 M0 = filename:basename(Beam),
  282: 	 M1 = filename:rootname(M0),
  283: 	 M = list_to_atom(M1),
  284: 	 "asn1ct_eval_" ++ Group0 = M1,
  285: 	 Group = list_to_atom(Group0),
  286: 	 io:format("%%\n"
  287: 		   "%% ~s\n"
  288: 		   "%%\n", [M]),
  289: 	 asn1ct_func:start_link(),
  290: 	 [asn1ct_func:need({Group,F,A}) ||
  291: 	     {F,A} <- M:module_info(exports), F =/= module_info],
  292: 	 asn1ct_func:generate(group_leader())
  293:      end || Beam <- Beams],
  294:     ok.

  583: constraint_equivalence_abs(Config) ->
  584:     DataDir = proplists:get_value(data_dir, Config),
  585:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  586:     Asn1Spec = "ConstraintEquivalence",
  587:     Asn1Src = filename:join(DataDir, Asn1Spec),
  588:     ok = asn1ct:compile(Asn1Src, [abs,{outdir,CaseDir}]),
  589:     AbsFile = filename:join(CaseDir, Asn1Spec++".abs"),
  590:     {ok,Terms} = file:consult(AbsFile),
  591:     Cs = [begin
  592: 	      Constraints = element(4, Type),
  593: 	      Name1 = atom_to_list(Name0),
  594: 	      {Name,_} = lists:splitwith(fun(C) -> C =/= $X end, Name1),
  595: 	      {Name,Constraints}
  596: 	  end || {typedef,_,_,Name0,Type} <- Terms],
  597:     R = sofs:relation(Cs, [{name,constraint}]),
  598:     F0 = sofs:relation_to_family(R),
  599:     F = sofs:to_external(F0),
  600:     Diff = [E || {_,L}=E <- F, length(L) > 1],
  601:     case Diff of
  602: 	[] ->
  603: 	    ok;
  604: 	[_|_] ->
  605: 	    io:put_chars("Not equivalent:\n"),
  606: 	    [io:format("~s: ~p\n", [N,D]) || {N,D} <- Diff],
  607: 	    ct:fail(length(Diff))
  608:     end.

 1370: xref(_Config) ->
 1371:     S = ?FUNCTION_NAME,
 1372:     xref:start(S),
 1373:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1374:     Test = filename:dirname(code:which(?MODULE)),
 1375:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_directory(S, Test),
 1376:     Q = "X - XU - \".*_SUITE\" : Mod",
 1377:     UnusedExports = xref:q(S, Q),
 1378:     xref:stop(S),
 1379:     case UnusedExports of
 1380: 	{ok,[]} ->
 1381: 	    ok;
 1382: 	{ok,[_|_]=Res} ->
 1383: 	    ct:fail("Exported, but unused: ~p\n", [Res])
 1384:     end.
 1385: 
 1386: %% Ensure that all functions that are implicitly exported by
 1387: %% 'export_all' in this module are actually used.
 1388: 
 1389: xref_export_all(_Config) ->
 1390:     S = ?FUNCTION_NAME,
 1391:     xref:start(S),
 1392:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1393:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_module(S, code:which(?MODULE)),
 1394:     AllCalled = all_called(),
 1395:     Def = "Called := " ++ lists:flatten(io_lib:format("~p", [AllCalled])),
 1396:     {ok,_} = xref:q(S, Def),
 1397:     {ok,Unused} = xref:q(S, "X - Called - range (closure E | Called)"),
 1398:     xref:stop(S),
 1399:     case Unused -- [{?MODULE,otp_14440_decode,0}] of
 1400:         [] ->
 1401:             ok;
 1402:         [_|_] ->
 1403:             Msg = [io_lib:format("~p:~p/~p\n", [M,F,A]) || {M,F,A} <- Unused],
 1404:             ct:fail("There are unused functions:\n\n~s\n", [Msg])
 1405:     end.
